1703 Hillcrest Lane, Austin, TX 78721; Kimberly Marie Grimes, whose address is 1703 Hillcrest Lane, Austin, TX
78721 (referred to below sometimes as "Borrower" and sometimes as'"Owner"); FROST BANK, whose address is

78750 (referred to below as "Contractor").
CONTRACT FOR IMPROVEMENT$
CONSTRUCTION OF IMPROVEMENTS.
Contractor agrees to furnish and to pay for all labor and materials needed to construct the
Improvements in a good and workmanlike manner, according to the plans and specifications agreed upon by Owper and Contractor and
approved by Beneficiary, on the following terms and conditions:
Description of the Improvements. The word "Improvements" as used in this Contract for Improvements means" the Construction and
completion of all improvements contemplated by this Contract, including all work necessary to make the Property usable and complete for
the intended purposes. The Improvements include the following labor and materials:
Labor and materials to be used in the construction of a single family residence in accordance with approved plans and specifications.
Contract Price. Owner agrees to pay, or cause to be paid, to Contractor the sum of One Hundred Ninety-two Thousand Two Hundred
Sixty-seven & 00/100 Dollars ($192,267.00), a portion of which is to be advanced by Lender to Contractor at the request and for the
benefit of Owner as consideration for the construction of the Improvements.
Note Payable to Lender. In consideration of the advance of the Contract price, Owner has executed and delivered to Lender the Role-in The"
amount of One Hundred Eighty-four Thousand & 00/100 Dollars ($184,000.00).
No Work Commenced. This Contract is executed, acknowledged and delivered before any labor has been performed apd before am
material has been furnished for the construction of the Improvements.
Alteration and Extras. No alterations shall be made in the work shown or described by the plans and specifications, nor shall any dutra.
work or materials be charged or paid for, unless a separate estimate for such extra work is submitted in writing by Contractor to Owvies ,-
and agreed to in writing by them before the extra work is started. The additional amount to be paid for all extra work and materials so
agreed to and so furnished shall be a part of the Indebledness secured by the lien created by this Contract. Beneficiary, at its option and
subject to the execution of such additional loan documents as Beneficiary may require, may advance all or part of such additional ahoupt"
If Beneficiary elects not to advance such additional amount, Owner shall pay Contractor in cash upon completion of such extra work, and,
Contractor shall have a lien on the Property for the payment of such amount, which lien Contractor agrees shall be subordinate to the ligh
retained and transferred to Beneficiary in this Contract. All extra work done or material furnished without such agreement shall ta
considered as performed under the original Contract and no extra pay shall be demanded or allowed. To the extent any conflict should
